# Users Module Rules

## User Entity

Users can be:
- **Buyer** (buyer/orderer) - Creates service requests
- **Seller** (seller/performer) - Sends proposals on requests
- **Admin** (administrator) - Moderates content and manages platform

## User Fields

- `id` - Unique identifier
- `name` - User name
- `email` - Email address (unique)
- `password` - Password hash
- `avatar` - Avatar URL
- `role` - Role (buyer, seller, admin)
- `rating` - Average rating (0-5)
- `reviewsCount` - Number of reviews
- `isVerified` - Whether user is verified
- `memberSince` - Registration date
- `completedDeals` - Number of completed deals
- `location` - User location
- `xp` - Experience points for gamification
- `unlockedAchievements` - Array of unlocked achievement IDs
- `topAchievements` - Array of top achievement IDs for display
- `isBlocked` - Whether user is blocked
- `blockedUntil` - Block expiration date (if temporary)

## User Endpoints

- `GET /api/users/me` - Get current user data
- `GET /api/users/:id` - Get user by ID
- `GET /api/users/:id/requests` - Get user's requests
- `GET /api/users/:id/proposals` - Get user's proposals
- `GET /api/users/:id/reviews` - Get reviews about user
- `GET /api/users/:id/stats` - Get user statistics
- `GET /api/users/:id/achievements` - Get user achievements
- `PATCH /api/users/me` - Update current user profile

## User Service

- Handle user CRUD operations
- Calculate user statistics
- Update user rating after reviews
- Manage user XP and achievements
- Handle user blocking/unblocking

## Security

- Never return password hash in responses
- Validate email uniqueness
- Hash passwords using bcrypt
- Verify user ownership before updates
